1
00:00:00,398 --> 00:00:02,628
(It's 7am and the sun has not yet risen.)

2
00:00:02,868 --> 00:00:04,138
What is this?

3
00:00:05,038 --> 00:00:06,168
What's going on?

4
00:00:06,938 --> 00:00:09,507
- What... Why...
- Why are we wearing this?

5
00:00:09,508 --> 00:00:10,977
(Grumbling)

6
00:00:10,978 --> 00:00:12,338
What is this for?

7
00:00:12,508 --> 00:00:14,177
(Jong Min appears.)

8
00:00:14,178 --> 00:00:15,207
What are you guys doing?

9
00:00:15,208 --> 00:00:16,447
(Then Seon Ho enters.)

10
00:00:16,448 --> 00:00:18,178
I don't know. What are we doing?

11
00:00:18,878 --> 00:00:20,187
At the next shoot,

12
00:00:20,188 --> 00:00:23,658
we'll film the opening with you wearing your penalty outfits.

13
00:00:23,958 --> 00:00:24,987
Three seconds!

14
00:00:24,988 --> 00:00:26,858
(The rodeo dried persimmon challenge)

15
00:00:28,528 --> 00:00:29,528
You failed.

16
00:00:29,728 --> 00:00:30,997
Jong Min, you failed.

17
00:00:30,998 --> 00:00:32,027
You failed.

18
00:00:32,028 --> 00:00:33,228
(Jong Min and Joon failed.)

19
00:00:33,768 --> 00:00:34,798
You failed.

20
00:00:35,228 --> 00:00:36,237
He's angry.

21
00:00:36,238 --> 00:00:37,368
(After four fails)

22
00:00:37,698 --> 00:00:38,998
It looks like he'll manage.

23
00:00:39,268 --> 00:00:40,337
He might do it!

24
00:00:40,338 --> 00:00:41,668
Don't lose your helmet.

25
00:00:42,638 --> 00:00:44,978
(Perfect success)

26
00:00:46,848 --> 00:00:48,678
He never fails an eating mission.

27
00:00:48,748 --> 00:00:49,777
What is that?

28
00:00:49,778 --> 00:00:51,918
Look forward to these four dressing up.

29
00:00:52,278 --> 00:00:53,418
Only I survived.

30
00:00:54,548 --> 00:00:55,587
I didn't think...

31
00:00:55,588 --> 00:00:57,588
not eating the persimmon would backfire this hard.

32
00:00:58,188 --> 00:01:00,327
What am I getting dressed up as?

33
00:01:00,328 --> 00:01:01,587
(By 8am, they're all dressed up.)

34
00:01:01,588 --> 00:01:02,728
Is this even right?

35
00:01:03,058 --> 00:01:04,557
(How do they look?)

36
00:01:04,558 --> 00:01:05,728
Can we kick things off?

37
00:01:05,958 --> 00:01:07,127
Hello, dear viewers.

38
00:01:07,128 --> 00:01:09,067
2 Days 1 Night's endorphin, dopamine,

39
00:01:09,068 --> 00:01:11,137
and Fairy Laughter, that's me, Moon Se Yoon.

40
00:01:11,138 --> 00:01:12,167
We're at...

41
00:01:12,168 --> 00:01:13,938
(Today's destination)

42
00:01:14,608 --> 00:01:16,508
(It's 700m above sea...)

43
00:01:17,378 --> 00:01:19,608
(and snows a lot in the winter, )

44
00:01:20,448 --> 00:01:22,488
(making it a perfect place to enjoy winter sports.)

45
00:01:22,948 --> 00:01:25,877
(Pyeongchang)

46
00:01:25,878 --> 00:01:29,818
We're on the peak of Mount Balwang,

47
00:01:30,058 --> 00:01:31,658
which is 1,458m above sea.

48
00:01:32,118 --> 00:01:34,357
We hoped to film outdoors.

49
00:01:34,358 --> 00:01:35,658
(We wanted to shoot outside.)

50
00:01:35,988 --> 00:01:38,227
A cold wave alert was issued in the central areas as well as...

51
00:01:38,228 --> 00:01:40,708
east of North Jeolla Province and in North Gyeongbuk Province.

52
00:01:40,868 --> 00:01:43,968
(A cold wave alert was issued in Pyeongchang!)

53
00:01:44,368 --> 00:01:45,568
It's minus 20°C right now.

54
00:01:46,668 --> 00:01:48,267
(Extremely cold New Year's Day)

55
00:01:48,268 --> 00:01:50,137
(Cold Wave Alert for 10 Cities and Counties in Gangwon)

56
00:01:50,138 --> 00:01:51,837
(The new year brought in some frigid weather.)

57
00:01:51,838 --> 00:01:53,047
Our equipment froze...

58
00:01:53,048 --> 00:01:55,807
as well as the bottled water that we hoped to drink.

59
00:01:55,808 --> 00:01:57,747
That's the current situation.

60
00:01:57,748 --> 00:02:00,618
We had to shoot the opening indoors...

61
00:02:00,718 --> 00:02:02,818
to give our equipment time to thaw.

62
00:02:02,988 --> 00:02:04,487
I'm here alone right now,

63
00:02:04,488 --> 00:02:07,587
because, as you know, my colleagues are dressed up.

64
00:02:07,588 --> 00:02:09,727
What are they dressed as? How do they look?

65
00:02:09,728 --> 00:02:12,058
The crew had many long meetings...

66
00:02:12,458 --> 00:02:14,567
before deciding on the theme, "Se Yoon's Cells."

67
00:02:14,568 --> 00:02:15,868
(Se Yoon's Cells)

68
00:02:17,268 --> 00:02:20,368
(Se Yoon's the godfather of dress-up.)

69
00:02:20,838 --> 00:02:25,238
(He has many alter egos, also known as "cells.")

70
00:02:26,138 --> 00:02:27,747
(We chose just 4 and dressed up the others.)

71
00:02:27,748 --> 00:02:30,447
We prepared a Se Yoon collection for you to enjoy.

72
00:02:30,448 --> 00:02:34,018
All right. Se Yoon's Cells. Please come on in!

73
00:02:34,218 --> 00:02:35,218
Come on.

74
00:02:35,218 --> 00:02:36,218
(Come on!)

75
00:02:37,658 --> 00:02:38,738
This song is a masterpiece.

76
00:02:39,658 --> 00:02:41,187
(A slender man with pink hair...)

77
00:02:41,188 --> 00:02:42,428
(walks in shyly.)

78
00:02:45,728 --> 00:02:48,298
My gosh. That's great. That's Bookku Ho.

79
00:02:49,768 --> 00:02:52,138
Great. He took the music industry in 2021 by storm.

80
00:02:52,338 --> 00:02:53,908
The very first shy singer.

81
00:02:54,008 --> 00:02:55,507
"Introverts, don't hide."

82
00:02:55,508 --> 00:02:57,854
He showed that even the biggest introvert could pull this off.

83
00:02:57,878 --> 00:02:59,107
The iconic shy singer.

84
00:02:59,108 --> 00:03:00,578
(He's also stiff.)

85
00:03:00,948 --> 00:03:03,118
(Perfectly in sync)

86
00:03:03,418 --> 00:03:05,078
(I'm shy, but excited.)

87
00:03:05,818 --> 00:03:07,218
Oh, my. He even did a b-boy freeze.

88
00:03:07,348 --> 00:03:10,017
All right. That's it. Here's Bookku Ho.

89
00:03:10,018 --> 00:03:11,187
Come closer now.

90
00:03:11,188 --> 00:03:12,488
How do you feel today?

91
00:03:12,558 --> 00:03:14,027
- I'm very shy.
- Are you?

92
00:03:14,028 --> 00:03:15,487
- Hide since you're shy.
- What...

93
00:03:15,488 --> 00:03:17,227
What kind of life have you lived?

94
00:03:17,228 --> 00:03:19,027
No. It's okay. That was a wonderful song.

95
00:03:19,028 --> 00:03:20,504
- I can say that...
- Thank you for that.

96
00:03:20,528 --> 00:03:22,427
My part is only the tip of the iceberg.

97
00:03:22,428 --> 00:03:23,767
- Really?
- The lineup outside is amazing.

98
00:03:23,768 --> 00:03:25,337
- That explains why you're first.
- Right.

99
00:03:25,338 --> 00:03:26,807
- Our expectations will go up.
- Right.

100
00:03:26,808 --> 00:03:29,507
I'll bring in the second cell.

101
00:03:29,508 --> 00:03:30,637
Come on in.

102
00:03:30,638 --> 00:03:31,838
(The second cell enters.)

103
00:03:32,738 --> 00:03:35,907
(A man from the past...)

104
00:03:35,908 --> 00:03:38,078
(enters with a majestic soundtrack.)

105
00:03:39,348 --> 00:03:42,918
(Where have we seen this character before?)

106
00:03:43,488 --> 00:03:45,287
He's from the KBS drama.

107
00:03:45,288 --> 00:03:47,027
(He didn't play this character for a comedy show.)

108
00:03:47,028 --> 00:03:50,258
(It was Se Yoon's character in "Hong Gil Dong, the Hero!")

109
00:03:50,498 --> 00:03:53,798
(Portraying the sorrowful character)

110
00:03:54,168 --> 00:03:56,208
Keep reenacting the scene when you hear the arrows.

111
00:03:56,438 --> 00:03:57,598
It's Hwalbindang!

112
00:04:01,338 --> 00:04:03,038
That's it. Look at the camera.

113
00:04:04,178 --> 00:04:05,607
- That's it.
- Gom.

114
00:04:05,608 --> 00:04:07,508
(Sorrowfully)

115
00:04:07,948 --> 00:04:10,018
(Your emotional delivery is on point.)

116
00:04:13,188 --> 00:04:14,418
- What was the line?
- Cut!

117
00:04:14,988 --> 00:04:15,988
Come on.

118
00:04:15,989 --> 00:04:18,658
All right. Two of the cells have come out.

119
00:04:19,258 --> 00:04:21,227
Starting with the third one, it will be the main event.

120
00:04:21,228 --> 00:04:24,228
Everyone, look forward to seeing more of my cells.

121
00:04:24,358 --> 00:04:26,598
Third Cell, come on in.

122
00:04:28,768 --> 00:04:30,137
(Dainty feet)

123
00:04:30,138 --> 00:04:31,398
He looks tiny and cute.

124
00:04:32,368 --> 00:04:35,008
(His lips look especially thick.)

125
00:04:35,568 --> 00:04:38,737
(I am...)

126
00:04:38,738 --> 00:04:41,778
(so pretty.)

127
00:04:43,948 --> 00:04:45,378
Hello.

128
00:04:45,778 --> 00:04:47,417
Please stand at the photo spot.

129
00:04:47,418 --> 00:04:48,487
Hello.

130
00:04:48,488 --> 00:04:50,918
(Cell Go Eun Ae, seeking love)

131
00:04:51,158 --> 00:04:52,358
He looks like a real baby.

132
00:04:52,718 --> 00:04:54,957
- DinDin looks like a baby.
- Like an elementary school kid.

133
00:04:54,958 --> 00:04:56,257
Hello.

134
00:04:56,258 --> 00:04:57,398
- Where...
- Yes.

135
00:04:57,498 --> 00:04:59,558
Your makeup session began at 6am, right?

136
00:04:59,698 --> 00:05:00,698
It was slightly after 6am.

137
00:05:00,698 --> 00:05:01,698
- It was slightly after 6am.
- Yes.

138
00:05:01,699 --> 00:05:02,727
Let me tell you now.

139
00:05:02,728 --> 00:05:05,837
After two hours, your makeup will permanently be part of your skin.

140
00:05:05,838 --> 00:05:06,867
- Like my lips?
- Yes.

141
00:05:06,868 --> 00:05:08,407
I have another project tomorrow. Am I going to be okay?

142
00:05:08,408 --> 00:05:10,178
- Sure. It will be great and funny.
- Okay.

143
00:05:10,378 --> 00:05:11,577
- I love it.
- The third cell...

144
00:05:11,578 --> 00:05:12,837
was Go Eun Ae, played by DinDin.

145
00:05:12,838 --> 00:05:13,908
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

146
00:05:14,078 --> 00:05:16,448
Everyone, here comes the highlight.

147
00:05:17,148 --> 00:05:19,624
It's one of my favorite characters. The best character of my life.

148
00:05:19,648 --> 00:05:20,787
Come on in.

149
00:05:20,788 --> 00:05:22,588
(The last cell enters.)

150
00:05:24,488 --> 00:05:26,828
2 Days...

151
00:05:28,158 --> 00:05:29,158
(Laughing)

152
00:05:30,298 --> 00:05:31,927
(2 Days...)

153
00:05:31,928 --> 00:05:33,057
- 2 Days...
- He startled me.

154
00:05:33,058 --> 00:05:34,227
(He just looks like himself.)

155
00:05:34,228 --> 00:05:35,268
Your suit will rip.

156
00:05:35,698 --> 00:05:38,098
(He showcased his character on "Comedy Big League.")

157
00:05:39,038 --> 00:05:41,437
(A dim-witted assistant, Jo Soo Bong)

158
00:05:41,438 --> 00:05:42,438
- Do it again.
- 2 Days...

159
00:05:42,439 --> 00:05:44,077
- 2 Days...
- 2 Days...

160
00:05:44,078 --> 00:05:45,907
(Mimicking his character perfectly)

161
00:05:45,908 --> 00:05:47,708
Wait. What comes after 2 Days?

162
00:05:48,808 --> 00:05:49,878
1 Night.

163
00:05:51,718 --> 00:05:53,947
(The owner of the cells is greatly satisfied.)

164
00:05:53,948 --> 00:05:55,087
2 Days...

165
00:05:55,088 --> 00:05:56,088
(Going wild)

166
00:05:56,089 --> 00:05:57,758
2 Days...

167
00:05:58,288 --> 00:05:59,418
This is insane.

168
00:06:00,188 --> 00:06:01,227
What on earth...

169
00:06:01,228 --> 00:06:02,228
(An encore)

170
00:06:02,229 --> 00:06:04,497
Hey, this is crazy. My gosh.

171
00:06:04,498 --> 00:06:06,198
- Goodness.
- Okay. Great job.

172
00:06:06,358 --> 00:06:08,868
I've invited out all of Se Yoon's Cells.

173
00:06:09,128 --> 00:06:10,737
- Let's take a group picture.
- Yes.

174
00:06:10,738 --> 00:06:12,538
Let's take a group picture.

175
00:06:12,998 --> 00:06:14,537
(Se Yoon's Cells: What kind of cell will make the world laugh next?)

176
00:06:14,538 --> 00:06:16,107
What a crazy sight. This is a masterpiece.

177
00:06:16,108 --> 00:06:17,538
This dress-up session was divine.

178
00:06:17,638 --> 00:06:19,007
When I was getting the makeup done,

179
00:06:19,008 --> 00:06:20,347
- I was really stressed out.
- Why?

180
00:06:20,348 --> 00:06:21,477
- Why?
- I was like,

181
00:06:21,478 --> 00:06:22,647
"What am I doing here at dawn?"

182
00:06:22,648 --> 00:06:24,448
Then Jong Min was next to me.

183
00:06:24,848 --> 00:06:26,378
Afterward, I couldn't say anything.

184
00:06:26,548 --> 00:06:27,548
I bet.

185
00:06:27,848 --> 00:06:29,747
Are you happy with how your character came out?

186
00:06:29,748 --> 00:06:31,517
- Yes, I am.
- Right. And it's funny too.

187
00:06:31,518 --> 00:06:33,358
It's funny. I don't have to do anything...

188
00:06:33,528 --> 00:06:34,888
to make people laugh.

189
00:06:36,288 --> 00:06:37,297
- Right.
- Yes.

190
00:06:37,298 --> 00:06:38,727
- At restaurants...
- Wait.

191
00:06:38,728 --> 00:06:40,627
Who is this beggar? Did you play a beggar too?

192
00:06:40,628 --> 00:06:41,697
He's not a beggar.

193
00:06:41,698 --> 00:06:43,637
- He's Yeon from Hwalbindang.
- From "Hong Gil Dong, the Hero!"

194
00:06:43,638 --> 00:06:45,498
He's Go Eun Ae. You had the easiest character.

195
00:06:46,238 --> 00:06:47,338
He looks cute.

196
00:06:47,538 --> 00:06:48,807
He looks like an idol star.

197
00:06:48,808 --> 00:06:50,248
- Like a female idol star.
- Really?

198
00:06:50,378 --> 00:06:53,507
By the way, it's freezing outside today.

199
00:06:53,508 --> 00:06:55,807
This has to be the coldest weather while shooting our show.

200
00:06:55,808 --> 00:06:58,047
How would you rank today's weather?

201
00:06:58,048 --> 00:07:01,448
I rarely saw temperatures below zero in the double digits.

202
00:07:01,688 --> 00:07:03,517
When I checked earlier, it was at minus 19.7°C.

203
00:07:03,518 --> 00:07:04,717
(The temperature at dawn: Minus 19.7°C)

204
00:07:04,718 --> 00:07:06,087
- Minus 19.7°C?
- Yes.

205
00:07:06,088 --> 00:07:07,828
- Minus 19.7°C.
- Below 0?

206
00:07:07,928 --> 00:07:10,134
- Not the apparent temperature?
- It was the actual temperature.

207
00:07:10,158 --> 00:07:11,228
The actual temperature.

208
00:07:11,628 --> 00:07:13,444
What's going on? It's the soundtrack to "Goblin."

209
00:07:13,468 --> 00:07:14,497
What's going on?

210
00:07:14,498 --> 00:07:16,004
- It's the soundtrack to "Goblin."
- Is there more?

211
00:07:16,028 --> 00:07:17,148
I know the answer. "Goblin."

212
00:07:17,638 --> 00:07:18,938
- What?
- What?

213
00:07:19,568 --> 00:07:20,607
- What's going on?
- What?

214
00:07:20,608 --> 00:07:21,848
- There are two people?
- What?

215
00:07:22,038 --> 00:07:23,437
- Who are they?
- It's Kim Jae Won!

216
00:07:23,438 --> 00:07:24,938
(They have visitors?)

217
00:07:26,438 --> 00:07:28,747
(Given the soundtrack and the long coat, )

218
00:07:28,748 --> 00:07:32,148
(could it be Gong Yoo from "Goblin?")

219
00:07:34,518 --> 00:07:37,988
(Boom, Gong Yoo's lookalike for 0.001 seconds)

220
00:07:38,118 --> 00:07:39,118
(Laughing)

221
00:07:39,558 --> 00:07:41,428
This is so random. Isn't it?

222
00:07:41,788 --> 00:07:42,888
- Wait.
- What?

223
00:07:44,158 --> 00:07:47,298
(A good-looking man is next to Boom.)

224
00:07:48,768 --> 00:07:52,968
(A handsome face everyone wants to engrave in their eyes)

225
00:07:54,768 --> 00:07:56,567
("Our Blues")

226
00:07:56,568 --> 00:07:58,437
("The Tale of Lady Ok")

227
00:07:58,438 --> 00:08:00,707
("The Trauma Code: Heroes on Call")

228
00:08:00,708 --> 00:08:03,518
(After starring in major dramas, )

229
00:08:04,948 --> 00:08:07,447
(he established himself...)

230
00:08:07,448 --> 00:08:11,188
(as everyone's first love in "You and Everything Else.")

231
00:08:12,518 --> 00:08:16,127
(Kim Jae Won, the rising star)

232
00:08:16,128 --> 00:08:17,228
It's Kim Jae Won!

233
00:08:17,828 --> 00:08:19,027
- What?
- It's Kim Jae Won!

234
00:08:19,028 --> 00:08:21,168
(Everyone gets up when a rising star enters.)

235
00:08:22,298 --> 00:08:23,438
- It's Kim Jae Won!
- What?

236
00:08:23,868 --> 00:08:25,198
- What?
- It's Kim Jae Won!

237
00:08:25,298 --> 00:08:26,398
What's going on?

238
00:08:27,938 --> 00:08:31,007
(Today's surprise guests: Kim Jae Won and Boom)

239
00:08:31,008 --> 00:08:32,008
What?

240
00:08:32,678 --> 00:08:34,877
(Executing a performance upon entering)

241
00:08:34,878 --> 00:08:35,978
(Laughing)

242
00:08:37,978 --> 00:08:40,547
(Showing off their chemistry as soon as they come in)

243
00:08:40,548 --> 00:08:42,047
- This is so random. Isn't it?
- Hello.

244
00:08:42,048 --> 00:08:43,817
- Hello.
- Hey!

245
00:08:43,818 --> 00:08:46,017
- At the Entertainment Awards...
- I'm Boom.

246
00:08:46,018 --> 00:08:47,588
- Hello.
- Jae Won.

247
00:08:48,158 --> 00:08:49,258
- Hello.
- What's going on?

248
00:08:49,998 --> 00:08:51,257
- Hello.
- What is it?

249
00:08:51,258 --> 00:08:52,698
- What?
- Hello.

250
00:08:52,798 --> 00:08:54,528
You guys look great today.

251
00:08:55,468 --> 00:08:57,438
Are you dressed up as Mr. Bogus today?

252
00:08:57,838 --> 00:09:00,867
(Are you all right? You must've been startled.)

253
00:09:00,868 --> 00:09:02,838
I acted like a big brother around Jae Won.

254
00:09:03,268 --> 00:09:04,708
I'm meeting him, looking like this.

255
00:09:05,508 --> 00:09:07,377
- Come here.
- All right.

256
00:09:07,378 --> 00:09:09,447
No, don't look so serious. Can't you be funny?

257
00:09:09,448 --> 00:09:12,817
Actually, I had something in mind. The walk-on song didn't suit me.

258
00:09:12,818 --> 00:09:14,287
- I brought my own song.
- You did?

259
00:09:14,288 --> 00:09:15,288
Yes.

260
00:09:18,118 --> 00:09:19,217
(The mood changes instantly.)

261
00:09:19,218 --> 00:09:21,058
What are you doing there? Join him.

