- That sounds fun.
- We'll make...

510
00:16:46,898 --> 00:16:48,437
unforgettable memories...

511
00:16:48,438 --> 00:16:50,808
with two of our avid viewers today.

512
00:16:51,178 --> 00:16:53,907
It will be a team match of 3 versus 4.

513
00:16:53,908 --> 00:16:55,777
- It's 3 versus 4?
- It's a team match?

514
00:16:55,778 --> 00:16:57,077
- How fascinating.
- My gosh.

515
00:16:57,078 --> 00:17:00,048
It's a workshop. So I expect you to show us your teamwork.

516
00:17:00,248 --> 00:17:02,247
Your goal is to acquire as many faces of a dice as possible.

517
00:17:02,248 --> 00:17:03,248
- Okay.
- Okay.

518
00:17:03,249 --> 00:17:05,718
The winning team of the final toss...

519
00:17:06,488 --> 00:17:08,728
will get to eat a meal with wild pine mushrooms...

520
00:17:09,058 --> 00:17:11,074
which will invigorate your body in this cold winter.

521
00:17:11,098 --> 00:17:13,197
- Pine mushrooms?
- This area is famous for them.

522
00:17:13,198 --> 00:17:14,397
- We have to eat them.
- Wild pine mushrooms.

523
00:17:14,398 --> 00:17:16,027
- You must try to win more points.
- That sounds so good.

524
00:17:16,028 --> 00:17:17,567
- We must have wild pine mushrooms.
- You must like wild pine mushrooms.

525
00:17:17,568 --> 00:17:18,967
- I do.
- We must get some.

526
00:17:18,968 --> 00:17:19,997
- We ought to have them.
- Gosh, they sound great.

527
00:17:19,998 --> 00:17:21,267
With perilla oil...

528
00:17:21,268 --> 00:17:22,368
- and salt.
- Hey.

529
00:17:22,408 --> 00:17:23,408
- That's right.
- I eat them fresh.

530
00:17:23,408 --> 00:17:24,408
I just tear them by hand.

531
00:17:24,409 --> 00:17:25,537
- You eat them fresh?
- I don't grill them.

532
00:17:25,538 --> 00:17:26,707
- You don't grill them?
- That's how you eat...

533
00:17:26,708 --> 00:17:27,777
- Right.
- pine mushrooms.

534
00:17:27,778 --> 00:17:28,847
- You eat them fresh...
- You eat them fresh.

535
00:17:28,848 --> 00:17:30,047
- Some people eat...
- with sesame oil and salt.

536
00:17:30,048 --> 00:17:31,447
- even the dirt around them.
- Right.

537
00:17:31,448 --> 00:17:32,647
- You just eat them fresh.
- Really?

538
00:17:32,648 --> 00:17:34,217
- Of course.
- Can you show it to us today?

539
00:17:34,218 --> 00:17:35,787
(You think?)

540
00:17:35,788 --> 00:17:36,818
All right.

541
00:17:38,158 --> 00:17:39,257
We'll assign you to teams.

542
00:17:39,258 --> 00:17:40,557
- We should divide into teams.
- So...

543
00:17:40,558 --> 00:17:41,927
- Wait. Shouldn't there be...
- Yes?

544
00:17:41,928 --> 00:17:43,287
A sense of suspense when you share that?

545
00:17:43,288 --> 00:17:44,428
- What?
- You...

546
00:17:44,758 --> 00:17:46,627
- He keeps scrolling through songs.
- You've been browsing songs.

547
00:17:46,628 --> 00:17:48,027
- Come on.
- It's not that. He...

548
00:17:48,028 --> 00:17:49,797
- No. Listen.
- You didn't even play any song.

549
00:17:49,798 --> 00:17:51,467
(Boom's weapon, his speaker and cell phone)

550
00:17:51,468 --> 00:17:52,767
- It's not that.
- Come on.

551
00:17:52,768 --> 00:17:54,767
If he says something odd, I'll blast the music.

552
00:17:54,768 --> 00:17:56,167
- That's your plan?
- I'll cover his voice with it.

553
00:17:56,168 --> 00:17:57,577
- Is the song on standby?
- My gosh.

554
00:17:57,578 --> 00:17:59,314
I'll mask his voice if he says something awful.

555
00:17:59,338 --> 00:18:01,548
He even added MBLAQ's songs to the playlist.

556
00:18:02,808 --> 00:18:04,688
- Gosh, look at that. Joon.
- He came prepared.

557
00:18:06,248 --> 00:18:07,388
You ought to like it.

558
00:18:09,648 --> 00:18:14,128
(The background music keeps playing.)

559
00:18:14,728 --> 00:18:16,988
(Having a blast)

560
00:18:17,528 --> 00:18:19,857
(Jukebox Boom is ready to play songs around the clock.)

561
00:18:19,858 --> 00:18:21,727
- Does he have separation anxiety?
- Hey.

562
00:18:21,728 --> 00:18:23,127
- He keeps scrolling through.
- Listen.

563
00:18:23,128 --> 00:18:24,597
- Do it. Let him do what he wants.
- The music...

564
00:18:24,598 --> 00:18:25,737
- Play the music.
- Let him do whatever he wants.

565
00:18:25,738 --> 00:18:27,658
- Is it an important announcement?
- Yes, it is.

566
00:18:29,408 --> 00:18:29,815
All right.

567
00:18:29,889 --> 00:18:31,809
- Is it an important announcement?
- Yes, it is.

568
00:18:33,100 --> 00:18:34,939
- All right. Your teams today...
- Hey!

569
00:18:34,940 --> 00:18:36,140
The music sounds so grand.

570
00:18:36,340 --> 00:18:37,639
- Jae Won, - It's Entertainment Awards.

571
00:18:37,640 --> 00:18:39,910
Jong Min, DinDin, and Seon Ho will team up.

572
00:18:40,680 --> 00:18:41,809
- We have four people on our team.
- Boom,

573
00:18:41,810 --> 00:18:43,280
Se Yoon, and Joon will team up.

574
00:18:44,050 --> 00:18:45,650
- I'm with Se Yoon and Joon.
- Yes.

575
00:18:45,910 --> 00:18:48,270
Wait. I missed that because of the music. Who's on my team?

576
00:18:48,450 --> 00:18:50,419
- I only heard the music. What?
- Come on.

577
00:18:50,420 --> 00:18:51,789
- Who's on my team?
- Could you repeat that?

578
00:18:51,790 --> 00:18:52,889
- Jae Won.
- Jae Won.

579
00:18:52,890 --> 00:18:54,589
Jae Won, Jong Min, DinDin...

580
00:18:54,590 --> 00:18:55,620
He played it again.

581
00:18:56,090 --> 00:18:58,429
I can't hear anything.

582
00:18:58,430 --> 00:19:00,729
- The audio engineers hate this.
- I can't hear a thing.

583
00:19:00,730 --> 00:19:01,959
- Say, "2026."
- Okay.

584
00:19:01,960 --> 00:19:03,129
- Include that in the announcement.
- What?

585
00:19:03,130 --> 00:19:04,130
- Include 2026.
- What?

586
00:19:04,130 --> 00:19:05,130
- Include the title.
- That's...

587
00:19:05,131 --> 00:19:06,499
- It's the winter workshop...
- "Today's teams."

588
00:19:06,500 --> 00:19:09,599
of 2026. Today's teams are...

589
00:19:09,600 --> 00:19:10,869
- Go ahead.
- What is it?

590
00:19:10,870 --> 00:19:12,739
(The Winter Workshop of 2026)

591
00:19:12,740 --> 00:19:14,610
(Team Jae Won, Team Boom)

592
00:19:15,340 --> 00:19:16,709
- I really don't want to go outside.
- My gosh.

593
00:19:16,710 --> 00:19:17,779
No. Why are we going outside?

594
00:19:17,780 --> 00:19:19,049
We do have to go out.

595
00:19:19,050 --> 00:19:21,249
- Do you have a song for that?
- Is there a good song for that?

596
00:19:21,250 --> 00:19:22,620
- I do.
- The exit song.

597
00:19:22,680 --> 00:19:26,860
All right. It's very cold outside.

598
00:19:27,020 --> 00:19:28,959
- We must get our energy up.
- Let's start our winter workshop.

599
00:19:28,960 --> 00:19:31,229
- Let's go out and have some fun.
- Gosh, we're in trouble now.

600
00:19:31,230 --> 00:19:32,760
All right. It's the winter workshop.

601
00:19:32,990 --> 00:19:35,830
- Let's do this!
- Let's go!

602
00:19:36,030 --> 00:19:37,370
Let's keep our energy up.

603
00:19:38,170 --> 00:19:40,669
- Everyone, line up.
- Yes!

604
00:19:40,670 --> 00:19:41,869
- What do we have to do?
- Grab each other's shoulders.

605
00:19:41,870 --> 00:19:43,640
- I don't know.
- How do we do this?

606
00:19:43,770 --> 00:19:45,510
- Grab the shoulders.
- Okay.

607
00:19:45,840 --> 00:19:47,439
- Check it.
- One. Like this.

608
00:19:47,440 --> 00:19:48,509
- Two.
- One.

609
00:19:48,510 --> 00:19:50,079
- Two.
- I hate it.

610
00:19:50,080 --> 00:19:51,080
(Loathing it)

611
00:19:51,081 --> 00:19:52,349
- Come on.
- Let's go.

612
00:19:52,350 --> 00:19:54,780
- Let's turn. That way.
- Get your legs up.

613
00:19:55,620 --> 00:19:57,119
- I hate this kind of vibe.
- Go.

614
00:19:57,120 --> 00:19:59,019
(This kind of morning dance is new to them.)

615
00:19:59,020 --> 00:20:00,159
What is this?

616
00:20:00,160 --> 00:20:01,389
(Despite the complaints, they seem happy.)

617
00:20:01,390 --> 00:20:02,460
What is this?

618
00:20:03,120 --> 00:20:04,990
You're trying to delay going out.

619
00:20:05,190 --> 00:20:06,950
- Let's have some fun.
- We'll never go out.

620
00:20:09,000 --> 00:20:10,400
Why aren't we going out?

621
00:20:11,100 --> 00:20:13,399
(Quiet down. He's in the middle of a transition.)

622
00:20:13,400 --> 00:20:14,969
The DJ is here.

623
00:20:14,970 --> 00:20:16,499
- Why aren't we going out?
- Come on.

624
00:20:16,500 --> 00:20:17,570
(DJ Boom is here.)

625
00:20:19,040 --> 00:20:20,739
- What?
- Go!

626
00:20:20,740 --> 00:20:22,810
- Jump!
- This isn't what we do on our show.

627
00:20:23,340 --> 00:20:25,049
(So what?)

628
00:20:25,050 --> 00:20:26,080
(Laughing)

629
00:20:26,880 --> 00:20:29,149
(The stage is where I stand.)

630
00:20:29,150 --> 00:20:30,350
Raise your hands up.

631
00:20:30,950 --> 00:20:32,150
(Jumping)

632
00:20:32,620 --> 00:20:34,089
This doesn't seem to end.

633
00:20:34,090 --> 00:20:36,319
(They give their all to the opening segment.)

634
00:20:36,320 --> 00:20:37,860
(Coming up soon)

635
00:20:38,130 --> 00:20:40,500
(For the first time on our show...)

636
00:20:43,570 --> 00:20:44,570
(Cheering)

637
00:20:44,700 --> 00:20:49,639
(The most cheerful vibe in the history of our show)

638
00:20:49,640 --> 00:20:51,140
- Eat it.
- Eat it, Jae Won.

639
00:20:51,740 --> 00:20:53,510
(Are you leaving after lunch?)

640
00:20:53,840 --> 00:20:55,079
(It's okay as long as we're in love.)

641
00:20:55,080 --> 00:20:56,310
(Come on.)

642
00:20:56,540 --> 00:20:59,310
(The cutest request in the history of our show)

643
00:20:59,780 --> 00:21:01,380
(He relies on his looks a lot.)

644
00:21:03,180 --> 00:21:06,090
(We're joined by Boom and Kim Jae Won.)

645
00:21:06,390 --> 00:21:08,260
(Korea's best...)

646
00:21:08,490 --> 00:21:10,530
(Hey, why do you keep calling the shots?)

647
00:21:10,630 --> 00:21:14,960
(real variety show)

648
00:21:15,800 --> 00:21:18,800
(I'm sacrificing a lot on the show.)

649
00:21:18,970 --> 00:21:21,470
(Stay tuned!)

650
00:21:22,600 --> 00:21:25,340
- It looks like Switzerland here.
- Yes, it's so stunning.

651
00:21:26,110 --> 00:21:28,110
(It's time to go back down.)

652
00:21:28,380 --> 00:21:29,439
By teams?

653
00:21:29,440 --> 00:21:30,810
- Do we ride with our team?
- Yes.

654
00:21:32,110 --> 00:21:33,749
I'll sit alone on the other side.

655
00:21:33,750 --> 00:21:34,780
We're getting in.

656
00:21:35,250 --> 00:21:38,320
(The team members bond with each other on their way down.)

657
00:21:38,890 --> 00:21:41,120
Will it be okay today?

658
00:21:41,160 --> 00:21:42,359
I wonder if it'll be okay today.

659
00:21:42,360 --> 00:21:46,230
We've been saying this even before the start.

660
00:21:46,560 --> 00:21:48,659
It feels like a crisis.

661
00:21:48,660 --> 00:21:49,999
- The weather is...
- I know.

662
00:21:50,000 --> 00:21:52,400
- unbelievably cold today.
- Right.

663
00:21:52,700 --> 00:21:54,039
Did you get some sleep last night?

664
00:21:54,040 --> 00:21:55,769
Yes, I got some sleep.

665
00:21:55,770 --> 00:21:57,039
- I knew that I needed it.
- Right.

666
00:21:57,040 --> 00:22:00,069
I told only the closest people around me...

667
00:22:00,070 --> 00:22:01,839
that I'd be on 2 Days 1 Night.

668
00:22:01,840 --> 00:22:02,840
Okay.

669
00:22:03,010 --> 00:22:04,530
- They asked if I'd be okay.
- Oh, no.

670
00:22:04,750 --> 00:22:06,526
- "Will you be okay?"
- When you told them about the show?

671
00:22:06,550 --> 00:22:08,226
- "Will you be okay?"
- They must be worried.

672
00:22:08,250 --> 00:22:09,820
I asked them, "How bad is it?"

673
00:22:10,750 --> 00:22:13,250
It's one of the coldest days we've had.

674
00:22:13,520 --> 00:22:14,559
On a day like this,

675
00:22:14,560 --> 00:22:16,490
how did you break ice and get in the water?

676
00:22:16,790 --> 00:22:17,790
- We just went in.
- Seriously.

677
00:22:17,791 --> 00:22:20,799
- You have to go in the water today.
- We might do it today.

678
00:22:20,800 --> 00:22:22,129
- Are we getting in the water today?
- Of course.

679
00:22:22,130 --> 00:22:24,869
A day like today is perfect for big events.

680
00:22:24,870 --> 00:22:26,699
"Is it cold today? That's a big event."

681
00:22:26,700 --> 00:22:28,439
- Everyone gets excited to do it.
- That's what we do in winter.

682
00:22:28,440 --> 00:22:29,769
Can't you go in cold water?

683
00:22:29,770 --> 00:22:31,769
If you go in cold water on a day like today,

684
00:22:31,770 --> 00:22:34,440
- you'd get a heart attack.
- Definitely.

685
00:22:34,540 --> 00:22:36,009
(His outlook on the world keeps expanding.)

686
00:22:36,010 --> 00:22:37,280
Then we'll perform CPR on you.

687
00:22:37,380 --> 00:22:38,880
- Seriously?
- This...

688
00:22:39,210 --> 00:22:40,996
- Wait a minute.
- Then we'll perform CPR on you.

689
00:22:41,020 --> 00:22:42,219
Seriously?

690
00:22:42,220 --> 00:22:43,920
A heart attack is considered a big event.

691
00:22:44,090 --> 00:22:45,090
A heart attack...

692
00:22:45,091 --> 00:22:47,089
(This place gets worse the more you hear about it.)

693
00:22:47,090 --> 00:22:48,520
Hey, he's having a heart attack.

694
00:22:49,990 --> 00:22:51,160
When you open your eyes,

695
00:22:51,960 --> 00:22:53,460
you say, "Gosh, that was tough."

696
00:22:53,860 --> 00:22:56,729
(Shocked)

697
00:22:56,730 --> 00:22:58,469
In other words, when it snows on Christmas Day,

698
00:22:58,470 --> 00:23:00,129
people get excited because it's a white Christmas.

699
00:23:00,130 --> 00:23:01,970
It's equivalent of a heart attack on the show?

700
00:23:02,540 --> 00:23:03,569
No way.

701
00:23:03,570 --> 00:23:05,309
This is a heart attack variety show.

702
00:23:05,310 --> 00:23:07,010
(He can feel the sudden difficulty spike.)

703
00:23:07,310 --> 00:23:10,110
(I'm in big trouble.)

704
00:23:10,510 --> 00:23:13,679
(What's going on with Team Boom?)

705
00:23:13,680 --> 00:23:15,449
This is my 1st time on 2 Days 1 Night,

706
00:23:15,450 --> 00:23:17,019
so could you give me an overview?

707
00:23:17,020 --> 00:23:19,549
I've only worked in the studio for a long time.

708
00:23:19,550 --> 00:23:21,436
They don't let you eat here. Are you okay with that?

709
00:23:21,460 --> 00:23:23,119
I'm okay with not eating.

710
00:23:23,120 --> 00:23:24,460
- Really?
- Yes.

711
00:23:24,630 --> 00:23:27,129
- What about sleeping?
- I can sleep anywhere.

712
00:23:27,130 --> 00:23:28,329
- Seriously?
- Yes.

713
00:23:28,330 --> 00:23:29,630
Even when it's 20°C below 0?

714
00:23:30,030 --> 00:23:31,369
(Gasping)

715
00:23:31,370 --> 00:23:33,699
- Inside a tent.
- That's no place for sleeping.

716
00:23:33,700 --> 00:23:35,339
No, that's impossible.

717
00:23:35,340 --> 00:23:38,110
Your nose freezes from breathing. You get frozen snot in the morning.

718
00:23:38,370 --> 00:23:39,970
In this weather,

719
00:23:40,510 --> 00:23:43,240
they wouldn't let us sleep outdoors.

720
00:23:43,280 --> 00:23:46,149
(Everything is possible on 2 Days 1 Night.)

721
00:23:46,150 --> 00:23:47,579
What's your success rate in games...

722
00:23:47,580 --> 00:23:49,626
- when you're on the same team?
- It's close to zero.

723
00:23:49,650 --> 00:23:51,319
- Does the other team win?
- They're much better.

724
00:23:51,320 --> 00:23:53,549
Come to think of it, why did they team us up like this?

725
00:23:53,550 --> 00:23:55,259
I bet they saw him as two people.

726
00:23:55,260 --> 00:23:57,230
Boom has a lot of fighting spirit.

727
00:23:57,330 --> 00:23:58,929
I'm confident in geography...

728
00:23:58,930 --> 00:24:00,189
- and memorization.
- That's great.

729
00:24:00,190 --> 00:24:01,629
- Really?
- Then we're good to go.

730
00:24:01,630 --> 00:24:03,329
Ask him questions on capital cities.

731
00:24:03,330 --> 00:24:04,929
(Giving a quiz to test him)

732
00:24:04,930 --> 00:24:06,899
When I said geography, I didn't mean capital cities.

733
00:24:06,900 --> 00:24:08,376
I meant the sense of direction when driving.

734
00:24:08,400 --> 00:24:09,769
I don't need GPS.

735
00:24:09,770 --> 00:24:11,039
Okay, that's good.

736
00:24:11,040 --> 00:24:13,169
- Memorization is also important.
- Give him a question anyway...

737
00:24:13,170 --> 00:24:14,379
about capital cities.

738
00:24:14,380 --> 00:24:16,209
- Joon knows many capitals.
- Let's do it for fun.

739
00:24:16,210 --> 00:24:17,280
Indonesia.

740
00:24:17,780 --> 00:24:18,949
It's Indochina.

741
00:24:18,950 --> 00:24:20,620
(Indochina, Indonesia)

742
00:24:20,980 --> 00:24:23,889
(It's a little embarrassing moment.)

743
00:24:23,890 --> 00:24:25,149
It's okay. Romania.

744
00:24:25,150 --> 00:24:26,366
(What's the capital of Romania?)

745
00:24:26,390 --> 00:24:28,159
(Will he guess correctly this time?)

746
00:24:28,160 --> 00:24:29,190
Lambid.

747
00:24:30,020 --> 00:24:31,859
- It's Bucharest.
- Bucharest.

748
00:24:31,860 --> 00:24:33,160
It sounded legit.

749
00:24:33,460 --> 00:24:35,159
- What did he say? "Lambid?"
- Yes.

750
00:24:35,160 --> 00:24:36,880
- He said Lambid with confidence.
- Lambid.

751
00:24:37,100 --> 00:24:38,230
The capital of Croatia.

752
00:24:38,500 --> 00:24:40,540
(His brain freezes at the sudden question.)

753
00:24:40,640 --> 00:24:41,840
You can't play it like that.

754
00:24:42,400 --> 00:24:43,939
Even if you're drawing a blank, you should say something like him.

755
00:24:43,940 --> 00:24:45,070
Watch how he does it.

756
00:24:45,240 --> 00:24:46,920
- The capital of Croatia.
- Remy Bonjasky.

757
00:24:47,740 --> 00:24:50,579
