2749
01:28:28,494 --> 01:28:29,523
(Bickering)

2750
01:28:29,524 --> 01:28:31,064
Don't look at this while eating.

2751
01:28:31,164 --> 01:28:32,433
I'm eating potatoes with kimchi.

2752
01:28:32,434 --> 01:28:34,934
(Bickering)

2753
01:28:35,634 --> 01:28:38,974
(They are having different food in the same place.)

2754
01:28:39,934 --> 01:28:41,973
If I had to eat only one thing for the rest of my life,

2755
01:28:41,974 --> 01:28:42,974
it would be this.

2756
01:28:43,474 --> 01:28:44,714
- Is it that good?
- Yes.

2757
01:28:45,044 --> 01:28:46,073
This is...

2758
01:28:46,074 --> 01:28:48,683
(This is how a born entertainer washes his dishes.)

2759
01:28:48,684 --> 01:28:49,684
This is...

2760
01:28:49,685 --> 01:28:51,183
something I've never seen before.

2761
01:28:51,184 --> 01:28:52,753
He's showing many things today.

2762
01:28:52,754 --> 01:28:54,384
(Feeling refreshed)

2763
01:28:54,584 --> 01:28:57,224
Now, their energy levels are...

2764
01:28:57,594 --> 01:28:59,693
- completely different from ours.
- Yes.

2765
01:28:59,694 --> 01:29:01,763
Right. We've been nourished.

2766
01:29:01,764 --> 01:29:03,334
We've been recharged.

2767
01:29:04,194 --> 01:29:06,093
- Now that you're done eating, - Yes.

2768
01:29:06,094 --> 01:29:09,603
We will go to the next destination.

2769
01:29:09,604 --> 01:29:11,703
- We're going to the base camp now.
- Yes.

2770
01:29:11,704 --> 01:29:13,873
There will be two main games.

2771
01:29:13,874 --> 01:29:15,544
- Yes.
- Dinner Game...

2772
01:29:15,774 --> 01:29:17,273
- and Sleeping Indoors or Outdoors.
- Sleeping Indoors or Outdoors.

2773
01:29:17,274 --> 01:29:18,643
But it's really cold today.

2774
01:29:18,644 --> 01:29:19,644
Which one is more important?

2775
01:29:19,645 --> 01:29:20,784
This is a balance game.

2776
01:29:20,984 --> 01:29:23,114
Dinner Game or Sleeping Indoors or Outdoors?

2777
01:29:23,414 --> 01:29:24,414
(Hesitant)

2778
01:29:24,415 --> 01:29:26,284
I'd rather eat.

2779
01:29:26,514 --> 01:29:28,153
- Would you really?
- Yes, I don't mind.

2780
01:29:28,154 --> 01:29:30,694
I'm lucky enough to I fall asleep as soon as I lie down.

2781
01:29:30,794 --> 01:29:32,624
You've never slept in the minus 20°C cold.

2782
01:29:32,824 --> 01:29:33,923
- Have you?
- Outdoors?

2783
01:29:33,924 --> 01:29:36,164
No. What happens?

2784
01:29:36,394 --> 01:29:37,833
Do you know what happens?

2785
01:29:37,834 --> 01:29:39,194
- First, you freeze.
- You freeze.

2786
01:29:39,294 --> 01:29:40,703
- You freeze.
- You breathe.

2787
01:29:40,704 --> 01:29:42,133
- You breathe.
- Your face is so cold,

2788
01:29:42,134 --> 01:29:43,503
you try to cover it.

2789
01:29:43,504 --> 01:29:45,233
- Yes.
- Your breath freezes the cover.

2790
01:29:45,234 --> 01:29:47,504
It freezes. You get frostbite.

2791
01:29:47,544 --> 01:29:49,274
In that case, I want to sleep well.

2792
01:29:49,544 --> 01:29:51,843
We haven't experienced minus 20°C in a long time.

2793
01:29:51,844 --> 01:29:53,043
Yes. This is...

2794
01:29:53,044 --> 01:29:54,643
Even our Real Winter trips weren't this bad.

2795
01:29:54,644 --> 01:29:55,884
It wasn't this cold then.

2796
01:29:56,814 --> 01:29:58,013
Hey, guys, what's this?

2797
01:29:58,014 --> 01:30:00,654
The water's frozen solid.

2798
01:30:01,084 --> 01:30:03,283
Do we need to be afraid...

2799
01:30:03,284 --> 01:30:06,293
or can we relax a bit or something?

2800
01:30:06,294 --> 01:30:08,123
This bus makes me feel so uneasy.

2801
01:30:08,124 --> 01:30:09,993
- Why?
- We only rode a nice bus...

2802
01:30:09,994 --> 01:30:11,363
for the Real Winter Training Camp.

2803
01:30:11,364 --> 01:30:12,633
Do you know what that is?

2804
01:30:12,634 --> 01:30:14,464
- I know, but...
- We have no shelter.

2805
01:30:14,664 --> 01:30:15,664
What?

2806
01:30:16,364 --> 01:30:18,804
We slept outdoors shielded by a cardboard box.

2807
01:30:18,904 --> 01:30:20,004
We had to put them up.

2808
01:30:20,944 --> 01:30:24,874
(Just like this...)

2809
01:30:25,574 --> 01:30:26,674
I think we're here.

2810
01:30:26,914 --> 01:30:28,713
- What is it?
- It's not a bare mountain.

2811
01:30:28,714 --> 01:30:29,714
There's something.

2812
01:30:29,884 --> 01:30:31,413
- We're wrong.
- There must be a building.

2813
01:30:31,414 --> 01:30:32,983
- "There must be a building."
- Please give us a place...

2814
01:30:32,984 --> 01:30:34,684
- with a roof.
- Is there a building?

2815
01:30:34,884 --> 01:30:37,223
Can I have your attention, please?

2816
01:30:37,224 --> 01:30:38,693
- Yes.
- See? I'm worried now.

2817
01:30:38,694 --> 01:30:40,163
- What is it?
- I have a bad feeling.

2818
01:30:40,164 --> 01:30:41,193
What's wrong?

2819
01:30:41,194 --> 01:30:42,363
- I have a bad feeling.
- Don't.

2820
01:30:42,364 --> 01:30:43,593
- This is bad.
- Right here.

2821
01:30:43,594 --> 01:30:45,263
- What?
- You can get out for now.

2822
01:30:45,264 --> 01:30:46,463
- Okay.
- See?

2823
01:30:46,464 --> 01:30:48,203
- He wants us out.
- Get your stuff.

2824
01:30:48,204 --> 01:30:49,364
- We get out?
- Yes.

2825
01:30:49,604 --> 01:30:51,103
- We always leave the car.
- My goodness.

2826
01:30:51,104 --> 01:30:52,433
Why were you so solemn?

2827
01:30:52,434 --> 01:30:54,744
Joon, what do you think? Is this a bad start?

2828
01:30:54,904 --> 01:30:57,314
Well, he did say something he didn't have to.

2829
01:30:57,444 --> 01:30:59,244
- He could've just said, "Get off."
- Really?

2830
01:30:59,314 --> 01:31:00,983
"You can get out for now?"

2831
01:31:00,984 --> 01:31:02,714
I don't like how this feels.

2832
01:31:03,384 --> 01:31:05,414
What is it? What now?

2833
01:31:05,814 --> 01:31:07,783
What's up? Why do this to us?

2834
01:31:07,784 --> 01:31:09,453
- What now?
- From here onward...

2835
01:31:09,454 --> 01:31:11,153
- Yes.
- We can't...

2836
01:31:11,154 --> 01:31:13,153
take the bus to go any further.

2837
01:31:13,154 --> 01:31:14,423
We'll move in separate cars.

2838
01:31:14,424 --> 01:31:16,723
- Oh, cars? That's it?
- I got so worried.

2839
01:31:16,724 --> 01:31:18,293
- Really?
- I thought something was off.

2840
01:31:18,294 --> 01:31:19,493
Let's move in teams.

2841
01:31:19,494 --> 01:31:20,633
- Okay.
- Let's go.

2842
01:31:20,634 --> 01:31:21,864
(No... This is suspicious.)

2843
01:31:22,034 --> 01:31:24,403
Either car is fine. Get into whatever you want.

2844
01:31:24,404 --> 01:31:26,404
(The teams switch to smaller vehicles.)

2845
01:31:28,544 --> 01:31:29,644
I feel uneasy.

2846
01:31:30,744 --> 01:31:32,673
What do we do today?

2847
01:31:32,674 --> 01:31:33,814
I don't know.

2848
01:31:34,584 --> 01:31:36,044
I've been feeling weird.

2849
01:31:37,154 --> 01:31:40,284
(Anxious)

2850
01:31:41,454 --> 01:31:43,253
Why the sudden change in atmosphere?

2851
01:31:43,254 --> 01:31:44,524
It got tense.

2852
01:31:45,224 --> 01:31:46,623
This doesn't feel right.

2853
01:31:46,624 --> 01:31:48,323
You've been doing this for a while.

2854
01:31:48,324 --> 01:31:49,324
- Yes.
- Does it feel off?

2855
01:31:49,325 --> 01:31:50,434
Not off.

2856
01:31:52,864 --> 01:31:54,063
It feels really bad.

2857
01:31:54,064 --> 01:31:55,103
It feels really bad?

2858
01:31:55,104 --> 01:31:56,234
- Yes.
- I'm scared.

2859
01:31:56,834 --> 01:32:00,104
I don't see anything that could serve as a base camp.

2860
01:32:00,544 --> 01:32:02,574
Mr. Driver, does this seem bad to you?

2861
01:32:03,374 --> 01:32:05,074
- Yes.
- Does it?

2862
01:32:05,374 --> 01:32:07,414
He must've driven you around for a long time.

2863
01:32:07,684 --> 01:32:09,543
- Where...
- We're setting off.

2864
01:32:09,544 --> 01:32:10,953
(The two cars set off with an uneasy feeling.)

2865
01:32:10,954 --> 01:32:12,214
We're off.

2866
01:32:12,254 --> 01:32:14,724
I'll tell you one thing I'm sure of.

2867
01:32:15,054 --> 01:32:16,123
It's not good.

2868
01:32:16,124 --> 01:32:18,253
We'd have walked up if it were good,

2869
01:32:18,254 --> 01:32:19,753
saying, "Hey, this place is gorgeous."

2870
01:32:19,754 --> 01:32:21,093
Oh, really?

2871
01:32:21,094 --> 01:32:22,693
Why can't the bus go any further?

2872
01:32:22,694 --> 01:32:24,333
The road's narrow. Why would that be?

2873
01:32:24,334 --> 01:32:25,593
- We're going up.
- It's rough terrain.

2874
01:32:25,594 --> 01:32:26,693
It's rough.

2875
01:32:26,694 --> 01:32:28,463
It's not too bad...

2876
01:32:28,464 --> 01:32:29,763
if the road is paved.

2877
01:32:29,764 --> 01:32:31,474
And there still are some buildings.

2878
01:32:31,574 --> 01:32:33,903
- The buildings disappeared.
- Really?

2879
01:32:33,904 --> 01:32:35,674
That was the last structure.

2880
01:32:36,444 --> 01:32:38,725
(The structures vanished as soon as they were mentioned.)

2881
01:32:39,374 --> 01:32:41,383
(Not long after that)

2882
01:32:41,384 --> 01:32:42,520
Something's coming. What's that?

2883
01:32:42,544 --> 01:32:45,654
(Their worrisome imagination soon becomes a reality.)

2884
01:32:46,114 --> 01:32:47,784
(Wind-chill temperature: minus 20°C)

2885
01:32:48,084 --> 01:32:51,054
(In the worst cold ever, )

2886
01:32:51,854 --> 01:32:54,824
(they must survive.)

2887
01:32:55,524 --> 01:32:56,593
(A frantic struggle...)

2888
01:32:56,594 --> 01:32:58,494
(for survival)

2889
01:32:58,694 --> 01:33:00,664
(They work together, )

2890
01:33:01,164 --> 01:33:03,734
(but something's going wrong!)

2891
01:33:04,404 --> 01:33:06,233
(Their friendship...)

2892
01:33:06,234 --> 01:33:08,474
(takes a tumble.)

2893
01:33:10,044 --> 01:33:11,643
- What are you doing?
- You're the worst.

2894
01:33:11,644 --> 01:33:13,074
(Utter shock)

2895
01:33:13,814 --> 01:33:16,114
(Did Jae Won turn evil?)

2896
01:33:16,584 --> 01:33:19,614
(Will they just crumble?)

2897
01:33:20,554 --> 01:33:25,424
(Do you want to see how their Real Winter unravels?)

2898
01:33:25,554 --> 01:33:26,793
You wanted to rest!

2899
01:33:26,794 --> 01:33:28,624
(See you next week.)
